[[WP:AES|←]]Created page with 'Battle of Chkheri - the battle of the Imereti kingdom against the Ottoman army during the Russo-Ottoman war of 1768-1774 (in the Chkherimel river valley). Held on February 6, 1774.  In 1773, Solomon I and Erekle II signed a military treaty against the Ottomans. In the same year, the kings together with 11 thousand cavalry marched in Javakheti, took Akhalkalaki, reached Kars and Ardahan. The Pasha of Akhaltsikhe could not resist, they would have released Sam...'

[[WP:AES|←]]Created page with 'Battle of Alinja - a battle between the armies of the Kingdom of Georgia and Tamerlane. In 1398, Tamerlane went to conquer India. The Kingdom of Georgia, the people of Sirvan and the Armenians took advantage of this, united under the flag of George VII and decided to drive out Temur's garrisons near the Caucasus. Georgians were joined by Ali Shakiseli and they started towards Alinja Castle. All this was reported to Miran-Shah, the son of Tamerlane in Tabriz...'

[[WP:AES|←]]Created page with 'Battle of Botori — a battle between the Georgian army and the Seljuk Empire on February 14, 1120.  In February 1120, David the builder first moved to Geguti, and from there to Khupati. The Seljuks "found out how far it was, they came down to Botora, the great ones, and spent the winter." On February 14, David attacked the Seljuks and completely destroyed them. As a result of the battle, the Georgians took many prisoners and captured a large army.'

[[WP:AES|←]]Created page with 'Battle of Botori a battle between the Georgian army and the Seljuk Turks on February 14, 1120.  In February 1120, David the builder first moved to Geguti, and from there to Khufati. The Seljuks "found out how far it was, they came down to Botori, the great ones, and spent the winter." On February 14, David attacked the Seljuks and completely destroyed them. As a result of the battle, the Georgians took many prisoners and captured a large army.'
